.TH _printf 3 "April 2026" i"_printf Manual" "Custom C Library"

.SH NAME
_printf \- custom implementation of printf function

.SH SYNOPSIS
#include "main.h"

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION
The _printf function prints output based on a format string.
It writes the result to the standard output (stdout).

The format string can include normal text and format specifiers,
which start with the '%' symbol.

Supported specifiers:
.TP
.B %c
Prints a character.
.TP
.B %s
Prints a string.
.TP
.B %%
Prints a percent sign.
.TP
.B %d, %i
Prints an integer.

If a NULL string is passed to %s, "(null)" will be printed.

The function uses helper functions such as:
.TP
.B _write_buffer
Stores characters in a buffer and prints them when needed.
.TP
.B print_int
Prints integers using recursion.

The function does not support flags or advanced formatting.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The _printf function returns the number of characters printed.
The null byte is not counted.

If something goes wrong, it returns -1.

.SH EXAMPLES
_printf("Hello %s\n", "world");
_printf("Number: %d\n", 10);
_printf("Char: %c\n", 'A');
_printf("Percent: %%\n");

